who is India's test captain?

Shubman Gill has been appointed as India's newest Test captain. He replaces the just-retired Rohit Sharma and will start his tenure with the upcoming five-match series against England starting on June 20 at Leeds. Shubman Gill is the 37th cricketer to captain India in Test cricket.
